'''''Chronos''''' (also known as '''''Chronos: A Tapestry of Time''''') is a [[shoot 'em up]] developed by The Radical Tubes and published by [[Mastertronic]] for the [[ZX Spectrum]] and [[Amstrad CPC]] in 1987. The music was scored by [[Tim Follin]]. The game received mixed reviews upon release.

==Plot==
Seven Ruling Lords create their own races, with Wodan creating man and Chronos creating the "Mystical Dimension Weavers".<ref>{{cite magazine|title=Future Shocks|date=June 1987|magazine=[[Your Sinclair]]|page=10|issue=18|url=https://archive.org/stream/your-sinclair-18/YourSinclair_18_Jun_1987#page/n11/mode/2up}}</ref>

==Development==
The game was scored by the then fifteen-year old [[Tim Follin]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gamasutra.com/view/news/97596/Playing_CatchUp_Tim_Follin.php|title=Playing Catch-Up: Tim Follin|last=Cifaldi|first=Frank|work=[[Gamasutra]]|publisher=[[UBM plc]]|date=September 26, 2005|accessdate=November 6, 2016}}</ref>

